CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 9, 1964, pg. 1 reads:" World-Wide Delegation - The nearly 900 delegates attending the Methodist General Conference in Pittsburgh is world-wide, representing many races that inhabit the globe. The Courier cameraman captured some of these in above pictures...Third picture: John A. Greene, superintendent, Chicago District; J.R. Washington, Bluefield, W.Va.; D. Trigg James, executive secretary, Southeastern Jurisdictional Council; J. Wood, Washington, D.C....-Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: John A. Greene, J.R. Washington, D. Trigg James, J. Wood, gathered in interior for the 1964 United Methodist Church General Conference
